// Passport onboarding Verify identity Next, we\'ll read your passport MRZ, then verify the secure NFC chip matches — same flow as our web demo. Use a passport with the chip symbol on the cover Remove thick covers, stickers, or metal objects Hold your phone flat against the passport — try the back cover first Powered by VerID Back Back to review We will read the machine-readable zone (MRZ) from your passport photo page, then use it to unlock the passport chip over NFC and show the data stored on the chip. Scan photo page Enter MRZ manually Scan the MRZ Open the camera scanner and align the two-line MRZ at the bottom of the photo page. A TD3 (passport) MRZ is required for chip unlock. Tap the button to open the MRZ camera. Hold your passport steady until the scanner finishes. You need a passport (TD3) for chip unlock. Scan MRZ Set DYNAMSOFT_LICENSE_KEY in gradle.properties (see BuildConfig) and sync Gradle. Check the MRZ we read. If anything looks wrong, edit it before continuing. Continue to NFC Edit MRZ Enter exactly two lines of 44 characters each (TD3 passport MRZ). MRZ line 1 MRZ line 2 Validate MRZ Back to MRZ scan Hold your phone to your passport Align the top edge of your phone with the passport cover near the chip symbol. Keep steady until the read finishes. Chip detected Reading passport data Securing session Rest the closed passport on the back of the phone over the NFC area (often upper/center, varies by model), then hold it still. When you hear a sound or feel a buzz, stay still — the read will start automatically. Reading the chip Keep the passport against the phone without sliding until this finishes. Unlocking the chip and reading data… Elapsed: %1$d s · usually 5–20 s If nothing happens after ~25 s, lift and re-seat the passport on the NFC spot, or try again from the error screen. Your passport was read NFC data from your e-passport chip Passport chip read Data received from NFC Passport checks Chip data validated Passport NFC chip Approved Verified Chip data (DG1) Portrait from chip (DG2) Raw MRZ from chip Continue to selfie check Selfie check Scan your face so VerID can compare it with the portrait stored on the passport chip. Passport holder Face match Passport portrait Live selfie 98% confidence Waiting for capture Captured Comparing faces… Capture selfie Capture again Comparing… Camera permission is needed to capture your selfie. Face match OK Digital ID ready Your passport chip, portrait, and selfie match are now combined into a local VerID credential. Credential Emergency ID N.Z. Traveller · %1$s QR Open Digital ID Could not read the chip Try NFC again Name Document number Nationality Date of birth (YYMMDD) Date of expiry (YYMMDD) Gender Issuing state Document code
